title: Charles White Harvest Talk Unmatted Print
description:
Print developed from Charles White’s Harvest Talk, 1953, from the Art Institute of Chicago’s collection.

Charles White is recognized for the richness of his graphic work and his paintings, which typically depict aspects of the history, culture, and life of African Americans.   Harvest Talk (1953), is one of six charcoal and carbon pencil drawings originally exhibited at ACA Galleries in New York in 1953. 

  • Print Reproduction
  • Image size: 15 x 10 in.
  • Poster size: 12 x 16 in.
  • Materials: Premium Cardstock
